versatile   

ver_sa_tile
ˈvɜːr_sə_tl

a/an + versatile + 名詞
Python is a versatile programming language.

主詞 + be 動詞 + versatile
This software is very versatile. 


A versatile employee：全方位的員工（例如：既能寫程式，又能跑業務，還能做專案管理）。
A versatile actor：戲路很廣的演員（既能演喜劇，也能演悲劇）。
A versatile tool：多功能工具（例如：瑞士刀）。
A versatile app：功能豐富的 App（這是在說 Notion，它能寫筆記、做看板、管預算）。
A versatile piece of clothing：百搭的衣服（例如：白襯衫，配西裝可以面試，配牛仔褲可以約會）。




I have a versatile tool 
I have a versatile wardrobe 
I have a versatile tool that can fix almost anything.
I have a versatile wardrobe for all seasons.



要繼續寫 就 配 "that"  或  "because" 
人： He is so versatile that he can play any role in the movie.
人： He is versatile because he has many different skills.

物： This tool is so versatile that you don't need to buy other gadgets.
物： This tool is versatile because it has five different functions.

穿搭： This black dress is so versatile that it suits both work and parties.
穿搭： This black dress is versatile because it matches any kind of shoes.

食物： Eggs are so versatile that you can use them in almost every meal.
食物： Eggs are versatile because they can be cooked in many different ways.







雇用:
hire a employee 
hire a versatile employee
The company wants to hire a versatile employee 
The company wants to hire a versatile employee who can handle different types of work.


尋找:
look for a tool
look for a versatile tool
Many people look for a versatile tool
Many people look for a versatile tool that can solve multiple problems at home.

打包:
pack a black dress 
pack a versatile black dress 
You should pack a versatile black dress for your trip
You should pack a versatile black dress for your trip because it suits any occasion.


